        "name": "Do different language versions of Scrabble have different numbers of tiles?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. While the English version uses 100 tiles, other languages vary. French and Dutch use 102 tiles. Italian uses 120 tiles. The number depends on the language's alphabet size, letter frequencies, and the desired game length. Languages with larger alphabets or more evenly distributed letter frequencies may need more tiles to maintain balanced gameplay." }
      },
